ers. For $\\mathrm{MA_2P_4}$,\nthe largest $d_{11}$ is up to 6.12 pm/V. Among the 22 monolayers,\n$\\alpha_1$-$\\mathrm{CrSi_2P_4}$, $\\alpha_1$-$\\mathrm{MoSi_2P_4}$,\n$\\alpha_1$-$\\mathrm{CrGe_2P_4}$, $\\alpha_1$-$\\mathrm{MoGe_2P_4}$ and\n$\\alpha_2$-$\\mathrm{CrGe_2P_4}$ have large $d_{11}$, which are greater than or\nclose to 5 pm/V, a typical value for bulk piezoelectric materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Dec 2020 08:31:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-29"}
